{{Infobox ancient site | name = Kai Chōshizuka Kofun | native_name = 甲斐銚子塚古墳 | native_name_lang = | image = Kai Choshizuka Kofun zenkei.JPG | image_size = | alt = | caption = Kai Chōshizuka Kofun | map_type = Japan Yamanashi Prefecture#Japan | map_alt = location in Japan | relief = 1 | map_caption = Kai Chōshizuka Kofun | map_size = 270px | altitude_m = | altitude_ref = | coordinates = {{coord|35|35|33|N|138|34|45|E|display=inline, title}} | map_dot_label = | location = [[Kōfu, Yamanashi]], [[Japan]] | region = [[Chūbu region]] | type = [[kofun]] | part_of = | length = | width = | area = | volume = | diameter = | circumference = | height = | built = 4th century AD | abandoned = | epochs = [[Kofun period]] | cultures = | discovered = | excavations = | archaeologists = | condition = | ownership = | management = | public_access = Yes | other_designation = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | architectural_styles = | architectural_details = |notes = {{box|background=white|align=center|wide=yes|border size=3px|border color=brown|text align=center|[[Monuments of Japan|National Historic Site of Japan]]}} }} [[file:甲斐銚子塚古墳出土 三角縁神獣車馬鏡.JPG|right|thumb|280px|Bronze Mirror excavated at the Kai Chōshizuka Kofun]] The {{nihongo|'''Kai Chōshizuka Kofun'''|甲斐銚子塚古墳|}} is a ''[[kofun]]'' [[burial mound]] located in the Shimosone neighborhood of the city of [[Kōfu, Yamanashi]] in the [[Chūbu region]] of [[Japan]]. Together with the adjacent {{nihongo|'''Maruyamazuka Kofun'''|丸山塚古墳| }} it was designated as a [[Monuments of Japan|National Historic Site of Japan]] in 1930.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/heritages/detail/138487 |title= 銚子塚古墳附丸山塚古墳 |trans-title= |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=August 20, 2020}}</ref> It is one of the largest keyhole-shaped tumuli in eastern Japan and has a total length of 169 meters. The tumuli are located a three minute walk from the "Kenritsukōkohakubutsukan" bus stop on the Yamanashi Kōtsu Ka